The code defines a class `EmojiUtil` with methods to check if a given Unicode code point or string is an emoji. The `isEmojiCodePoint` method checks specific Unicode ranges for emoji characters, and `isEmoji` checks if a string's first character is an emoji. The main method tests the utility with various strings.
```java
public class EmojiUtil {
    public static boolean isEmojiCodePoint(int code) {
        // 0x1F600 - 0x1F64F are Emoticons
        if (code >= 0x1F600 && code <= 0x1F64F) {
            return true;
        }
        // 0x1F300 - 0x1F5FF are Misc Symbols and Pictographs
        if (code >= 0x1F300 && code <= 0x1F5FF) {
            return true;
        }
        // 0x1F680 - 0x1F6FF are Transport and Map Symbols
        if (code >= 0x1F680 && code <= 0x1F6FF) {
            return true;
        }
        // 0x1F1E0 - 0x1F1FF are Regional Indicator Symbols
        if (code >= 0x1F1E0 && code <= 0x1F1FF) {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public static boolean isEmoji(String str) {
        if (str == null || str.isEmpty()) {
            return false;
        }
        int codePoint = str.codePointAt(0);
        return isEmojiCodePoint(codePoint);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
